title: Body On I-90
text:
October 1, 2015, 11:38 PM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
A body on Interstate 90 at mile marker 396 had traffic closed off. Westbound traffic was blocked from Cliff Avenue and mile marker 397 around 11 p.m. Thursday night. 
The Minnehaha County Sheriff’s Office is looking for a semi-truck and its driver which might have hit a victim. The Sheriff’s Office found a body at mile marker 397 on I-90. 
Deputies think a white semi-truck might have hit this victim and kept driving westbound. The Sheriff’s Office is looking for help in finding the truck and driver in what they’re calling an accident. 
The Sheriff’s Office also asks anyone who witnessed the incident to call Metro Communications at 605-367-7000. © 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
